### parseScalarValue() {#a8f168615fb43a51a70c57eee12a86038}

<MemberDefinition
  prototype={<>static StringRef parseScalarValue (<a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/stringref">StringRef</a> UnquotedValue, <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/smallvectorimpl">SmallVectorImpl</a>&lt; char &gt; &amp; Storage, <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/stringref">StringRef</a> LookupChars, <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/analysis/regionprinter-cpp/#aa37fbbce2360106772fd97ed06455d55">std::function</a>&lt; <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/stringref">StringRef</a>(<a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/stringref">StringRef</a>, <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/smallvectorimpl">SmallVectorImpl</a>&lt; char &gt; &amp;)&gt; UnescapeCallback)</>}
  labels = {["static"]}>
parseScalarValue - A common parsing routine for all flow scalar styles.

It handles line break characters by itself, adds regular content characters to the result, and forwards escaped sequences to the provided routine for the style-specific processing.


<ParametersList title="Parameters">
<ParametersListItem name="UnquotedValue">- An input value without quotation marks.</ParametersListItem>
<ParametersListItem name="Storage">- A storage for the result if the input value is multiline or contains escaped characters.</ParametersListItem>
<ParametersListItem name="LookupChars">- A set of special characters to search in the input string. Should include line break characters and the escape character specific for the processing scalar style, if any.</ParametersListItem>
<ParametersListItem name="UnescapeCallback">- This is called when the escape character is found in the input.</ParametersListItem>
</ParametersList>

<SectionUser title="Returns">
- The unfolded and unescaped value.
</SectionUser>

Definition at line <a href="#l02054">2054</a> of file <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/support/yamlparser-cpp">YAMLParser.cpp</a>.
</MemberDefinition>

<Link id="l00168" /><CodeLine lineNumber="168"><Highlight kind="comment">/// This struct is used to track simple keys.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00169" /><CodeLine lineNumber="169"><Highlight kind="comment">///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00170" /><CodeLine lineNumber="170"><Highlight kind="comment">/// Simple keys are handled by creating an entry in SimpleKeys for each Token</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00171" /><CodeLine lineNumber="171"><Highlight kind="comment">/// which could legally be the start of a simple key. When peekNext is called,</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00172" /><CodeLine lineNumber="172"><Highlight kind="comment">/// if the Token To be returned is referenced by a SimpleKey, we continue</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00173" /><CodeLine lineNumber="173"><Highlight kind="comment">/// tokenizing until that potential simple key has either been found to not be</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00174" /><CodeLine lineNumber="174"><Highlight kind="comment">/// a simple key (we moved on to the next line or went further than 1024 chars).</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00175" /><CodeLine lineNumber="175"><Highlight kind="comment">/// Or when we run into a Value, and then insert a Key token (and possibly</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00176" /><CodeLine lineNumber="176"><Highlight kind="comment">/// others) before the SimpleKey&#39;s Tok.</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00191" /><CodeLine lineNumber="191"><Highlight kind="comment">/// The Unicode scalar value of a UTF-8 minimal well-formed code unit</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00192" /><CodeLine lineNumber="192"><Highlight kind="comment">///        subsequence and the subsequence&#39;s length in code units (uint8&#95;t).</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00193" /><CodeLine lineNumber="193"><Highlight kind="comment">///        A length of 0 represents an error.</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00194" /><CodeLine lineNumber="194" lineLink="#a312eeacf9361f1c1516dbafdec94e500"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword">using </Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"><a href="#a312eeacf9361f1c1516dbafdec94e500">UTF8Decoded</a> = std::pair&lt;uint32&#95;t, unsigned&gt;;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00195" /><CodeLine lineNumber="195"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00196" /><CodeLine lineNumber="196" lineLink="#aee2537a5e509713ca8ae26bef2ed947e"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword">static</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> <a href="#a312eeacf9361f1c1516dbafdec94e500">UTF8Decoded</a> <a href="#aee2537a5e509713ca8ae26bef2ed947e">decodeUTF8</a>(<a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/stringref">StringRef</a> <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/target/lib/target/nvptx/nvvmintrrange-cpp/#a34bd74317e3f04bfc4318c2d1a470877">Range</a>) &#123;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00197" /><CodeLine lineNumber="197"><Highlight kind="normal">  <a href="/docs/api/classes/anonymous-namespace-path-cpp-/stringref/#a20d37563688a61a452fb26e317e37308">StringRef::iterator</a> Position= <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/target/lib/target/nvptx/nvvmintrrange-cpp/#a34bd74317e3f04bfc4318c2d1a470877">Range</a>.begin();</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00198" /><CodeLine lineNumber="198"><Highlight kind="normal">  <a href="/docs/api/classes/anonymous-namespace-path-cpp-/stringref/#a20d37563688a61a452fb26e317e37308">StringRef::iterator</a> End = <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/target/lib/target/nvptx/nvvmintrrange-cpp/#a34bd74317e3f04bfc4318c2d1a470877">Range</a>.end();</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00199" /><CodeLine lineNumber="199"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// 1 byte: &#91;0x00, 0x7f&#93;</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00200" /><CodeLine lineNumber="200"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// Bit pattern: 0xxxxxxx</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00201" /><CodeLine lineNumber="201"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="keywordflow">if</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> (Position &lt; End &amp;&amp; (&#42;Position &amp; 0x80) == 0) &#123;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00202" /><CodeLine lineNumber="202"><Highlight kind="normal">    </Highlight><Highlight kind="keywordflow">return</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> std::make&#95;pair(&#42;Position, 1);</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00203" /><CodeLine lineNumber="203"><Highlight kind="normal">  &#125;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00204" /><CodeLine lineNumber="204"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// 2 bytes: &#91;0x80, 0x7ff&#93;</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00205" /><CodeLine lineNumber="205"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// Bit pattern: 110xxxxx 10xxxxxx</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00206" /><CodeLine lineNumber="206"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="keywordflow">if</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> (Position + 1 &lt; End &amp;&amp; ((&#42;Position &amp; 0xE0) == 0xC0) &amp;&amp;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00207" /><CodeLine lineNumber="207"><Highlight kind="normal">      ((&#42;(Position + 1) &amp; 0xC0) == 0x80)) &#123;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00208" /><CodeLine lineNumber="208"><Highlight kind="normal">    uint32&#95;t codepoint = ((&#42;Position &amp; 0x1F) &lt;&lt; 6) |</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00209" /><CodeLine lineNumber="209"><Highlight kind="normal">                          (&#42;(Position + 1) &amp; 0x3F);</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00210" /><CodeLine lineNumber="210"><Highlight kind="normal">    </Highlight><Highlight kind="keywordflow">if</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> (codepoint &gt;= 0x80)</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00211" /><CodeLine lineNumber="211"><Highlight kind="normal">      </Highlight><Highlight kind="keywordflow">return</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> std::make&#95;pair(codepoint, 2);</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00212" /><CodeLine lineNumber="212"><Highlight kind="normal">  &#125;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00213" /><CodeLine lineNumber="213"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// 3 bytes: &#91;0x8000, 0xffff&#93;</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00214" /><CodeLine lineNumber="214"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// Bit pattern: 1110xxxx 10xxxxxx 10xxxxxx</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00215" /><CodeLine lineNumber="215"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="keywordflow">if</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> (Position + 2 &lt; End &amp;&amp; ((&#42;Position &amp; 0xF0) == 0xE0) &amp;&amp;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00216" /><CodeLine lineNumber="216"><Highlight kind="normal">      ((&#42;(Position + 1) &amp; 0xC0) == 0x80) &amp;&amp;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00217" /><CodeLine lineNumber="217"><Highlight kind="normal">      ((&#42;(Position + 2) &amp; 0xC0) == 0x80)) &#123;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00218" /><CodeLine lineNumber="218"><Highlight kind="normal">    uint32&#95;t codepoint = ((&#42;Position &amp; 0x0F) &lt;&lt; 12) |</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00219" /><CodeLine lineNumber="219"><Highlight kind="normal">                         ((&#42;(Position + 1) &amp; 0x3F) &lt;&lt; 6) |</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00220" /><CodeLine lineNumber="220"><Highlight kind="normal">                          (&#42;(Position + 2) &amp; 0x3F);</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00221" /><CodeLine lineNumber="221"><Highlight kind="normal">    </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// Codepoints between 55296 and 57343 are invalid, as</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00222" /><CodeLine lineNumber="222"><Highlight kind="normal">    </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// they are high / low surrogate halves used by UTF-16.</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00223" /><CodeLine lineNumber="223"><Highlight kind="normal">    </Highlight><Highlight kind="keywordflow">if</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> (codepoint &gt;= 2048 &amp;&amp;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00224" /><CodeLine lineNumber="224"><Highlight kind="normal">        (codepoint &lt; 55296 || codepoint &gt; 0xDFFF))</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00225" /><CodeLine lineNumber="225"><Highlight kind="normal">      </Highlight><Highlight kind="keywordflow">return</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> std::make&#95;pair(codepoint, 3);</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00226" /><CodeLine lineNumber="226"><Highlight kind="normal">  &#125;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00227" /><CodeLine lineNumber="227"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// 4 bytes: &#91;0x10000, 0x10FFFF&#93;</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00228" /><CodeLine lineNumber="228"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// Bit pattern: 11110xxx 10xxxxxx 10xxxxxx 10xxxxxx</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00229" /><CodeLine lineNumber="229"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="keywordflow">if</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> (Position + 3 &lt; End &amp;&amp; ((&#42;Position &amp; 0xF8) == 0xF0) &amp;&amp;</Highlight></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00302" /><CodeLine lineNumber="302"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// The following functions are based on the gramar rules in the YAML spec. The</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00303" /><CodeLine lineNumber="303"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// style of the function names it meant to closely match how they are written</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00304" /><CodeLine lineNumber="304"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// in the spec. The number within the &#91;&#93; is the number of the grammar rule in</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00305" /><CodeLine lineNumber="305"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// the spec.</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00306" /><CodeLine lineNumber="306"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">//</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00307" /><CodeLine lineNumber="307"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// See 4.2 &#91;Production Naming Conventions&#93; for the meaning of the prefixes.</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00308" /><CodeLine lineNumber="308"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">//</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00309" /><CodeLine lineNumber="309"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// c-</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00310" /><CodeLine lineNumber="310"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">//   A production starting and ending with a special character.</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00311" /><CodeLine lineNumber="311"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// b-</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00312" /><CodeLine lineNumber="312"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">//   A production matching a single line break.</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00313" /><CodeLine lineNumber="313"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// nb-</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00314" /><CodeLine lineNumber="314"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">//   A production starting and ending with a non-break character.</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00315" /><CodeLine lineNumber="315"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// s-</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00316" /><CodeLine lineNumber="316"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">//   A production starting and ending with a white space character.</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00317" /><CodeLine lineNumber="317"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// ns-</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00318" /><CodeLine lineNumber="318"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">//   A production starting and ending with a non-space character.</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00319" /><CodeLine lineNumber="319"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// l-</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00320" /><CodeLine lineNumber="320"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">//   A production matching complete line(s).</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00322" /><CodeLine lineNumber="322"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// Skip a single nb-char&#91;27&#93; starting at Position.</Highlight></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00325" /><CodeLine lineNumber="325"><Highlight kind="comment">  ///                  | &#91;0xFF00-0xFFFD&#93; | &#91;0x10000-0x10FFFF&#93;</Highlight></CodeLine>
